com.cubeia.firebase.api.mtt.lobby
Class DefaultMttAttributeMapper

java.lang.Object
  com.cubeia.firebase.api.mtt.lobby.DefaultMttAttributeMapper
All Implemented Interfaces:
AttributeMapper<MTTState>, MttAttributeMapper
public class DefaultMttAttributeMapper
extends Object
implements MttAttributeMapper

This is the default implementation used by the internal Firebase classes to map a table into a set of attributes. It can be used and extended by games that accesses the lobby themselves.

Author:
lars.j.nilsson

setRequiredValues

public static final void setRequiredValues(MTTState mtt,
                                           LobbyAttributeAccessor acc)

This method sets the required attributes which are need by Firebase. All internal values start with underscore, e.g. _ID.

Internal Values:

  • _nodeType : Node type, will be 'mtt'
  • _ID : ID of the tournament instance
  • _TOURNAMENT_ID : ID of the tournament logic
  • _LAST_MODIFIED : Time of last modification of the state
  • _CAPACITY : Tournament player limit
  • _SEATED : Number of registered players

Parameters:
table - Table to take values from, never null
acc - Lobby accessor, never null

toMap

public Map<String,AttributeValue> toMap(MTTState logic)
This method maps all DefaultMtteAttributes to values taken from the parameter table. The enum toString method will be used to generate the attribute names.
